  "text": "One of the applications of studying the developmental metabolics is to increase the chances of conceiving for females who are suffering from reproductive complications, or for livestock or other animals. This type of experiment requires that the sensing technology is noninvasive to ensure that no damage is done to the embryo. SECM is a promising sensing technology for such an application, and Shiku et al. have recently applied SECM to measure the oxygen consumption of single bovine embryos [CITATION_1] .",
